ous of any cache issues from previous tests. Using unique classes may help to trigger initialization on line 632.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class details**\\n\\nI’m thinking about naming the class `JavaMembersTest`. It seems I don’t need direct reflection here since I’m not using `java.lang.reflect`. However, I do need to consider that `GlobalSetter` is public, so there’s no direct reflection involved in that context. This makes me double-check the class’s structure to ensure everything aligns properly without needing reflection. It's all about simplifying things when possible!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Writing report for JavaMembersTest**\\n\\nI’m figuring out how to call sites that are active and included in the JavaMembersTest. That sounds good! I think it makes sense to focus on reporting the active class specifically, without adding any unnecessary metadata. So, my next step is to write that report file. It feels straightforward, but I want to be sure I'm sticking to what’s needed and nothing more. Let's keep it clear and concise!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_L0rvqAmUdY9O7G3KOGHZFWSG|fc_051786af27bb3399016a288e85464c8194a297f230dc09a304", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaMembersTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sourceforge_htmlunit.htmlunit_core_js;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Context;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ContextFactory;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeJavaClass;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ScriptableObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Wrapper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class JavaMembersTest {\n    private static final ContextFactory ORIGINAL_CONTEXT_FACTORY = ContextFactory.getGlobal();\n    private static final ContextFactory.GlobalSetter GLOBAL_SETTER = ContextFactory.getGlobalSetter();\n\n    @AfterEach\n    void restoreContextFactory() {\n        GLOBAL_SETTER.setContextFactoryGlobal(ORIGINAL_CONTEXT_FACTORY);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsAndWritesPublicJavaFieldsFromScript() {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            PublicFieldBean bean = new PublicFieldBean(\"initial\");\n            ScriptableObject.putProperty(scope, \"bean\", Context.javaToJS(bean, scope));\n\n            Object initialValue = context.evaluateString(scope, \"bean.text\", \"field-read\", 1, null);\n            Object updatedValue =\n                    context.evaluateString(\n                            scope,\n                            \"bean.text = 'updated'; bean.text;\",\n                            \"field-write\",\n                            1,\n                            null);\n\n            assertThat(Context.jsToJava(initialValue, String.class)).isEqualTo(\"initial\");\n            assertThat(Context.jsToJava(updatedValue, String.class)).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n            assertThat(bean.text).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void constructsClassWithPrivateConstructorWhenEnhancedJavaAccessIsEnabled() {\n        GLOBAL_SETTER.setContextFactoryGlobal(new EnhancedJavaAccessContextFactory());\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            NativeJavaClass javaClass = new NativeJavaClass(scope, PrivateConstructorBean.class);\n\n            Scriptable constructed = javaClass.construct(context, scope, new Object[] {\"created\"});\n\n            assertThat(constructed).isInstanceOf(Wrapper.class);\n            assertThat(((Wrapper) constructed).unwrap())\n                    .isInstanceOfSatisfying(\n                            PrivateConstructorBean.class,\n                            bean -> assertThat(bean.value()).isEqualTo(\"created\"));\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class PublicFieldBean {\n        public String text;\n\n        public PublicFieldBean(String text) {\n            this.text = text;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class PrivateConstructorBean {\n        private final String value;\n\n        private PrivateConstructorBean(String value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n\n        public String value() {\n            return value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EnhancedJavaAccessContextFactory extends ContextFactory {\n        @Override\n        protected boolean hasFeature(Context context, int featureIndex) {\n            if (featureIndex == Context.FEATURE_ENHANCED_JAVA_ACCESS) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            return super.hasFeature(context, featureIndex);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 179, "output": 2905, "cacheRead": 51200, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54284, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781042760115, "responseId": "resp_051786af27bb3399016a288e48c8a88194b130158994422838"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_L0rvqAmUdY9O7G3KOGHZFWSG|fc_051786af27bb3399016a288e85464c8194a297f230dc09a304 name=write args={"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaMembersTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sourceforge_htmlunit.htmlunit_core_js;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Context;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ContextFactory;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeJavaClass;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.ScriptableObject;\nimport net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.Wrapper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class JavaMembersTest {\n    private static final ContextFactory ORIGINAL_CONTEXT_FACTORY = ContextFactory.getGlobal();\n    private static final ContextFactory.GlobalSetter GLOBAL_SETTER = ContextFactory.getGlobalSetter();\n\n    @AfterEach\n    void restoreContextFactory() {\n        GLOBAL_SETTER.setContextFactoryGlobal(ORIGINAL_CONTEXT_FACTORY);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsAndWritesPublicJavaFieldsFromScript() {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            PublicFieldBean bean = new PublicFieldBean(\"initial\");\n            ScriptableObject.putProperty(scope, \"bean\", Context.javaToJS(bean, scope));\n\n            Object initialValue = context.evaluateString(scope, \"bean.text\", \"field-read\", 1, null);\n            Object updatedValue =\n                    context.evaluateString(\n                            scope,\n                            \"bean.text = 'updated'; bean.text;\",\n                            \"field-write\",\n                            1,\n                            null);\n\n            assertThat(Context.jsToJava(initialValue, String.class)).isEqualTo(\"initial\");\n            assertThat(Context.jsToJava(updatedValue, String.class)).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n            assertThat(bean.text).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void constructsClassWithPrivateConstructorWhenEnhancedJavaAccessIsEnabled() {\n        GLOBAL_SETTER.setContextFactoryGlobal(new EnhancedJavaAccessContextFactory());\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n            NativeJavaClass javaClass = new NativeJavaClass(scope, PrivateConstructorBean.class);\n\n            Scriptable constructed = javaClass.construct(context, scope, new Object[] {\"created\"});\n\n            assertThat(constructed).isInstanceOf(Wrapper.class);\n            assertThat(((Wrapper) constructed).unwrap())\n                    .isInstanceOfSatisfying(\n                            PrivateConstructorBean.class,\n                            bean -> assertThat(bean.value()).isEqualTo(\"created\"));\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class PublicFieldBean {\n        public String text;\n\n        public PublicFieldBean(String text) {\n            this.text = text;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class PrivateConstructorBean {\n        private final String value;\n\n        private PrivateConstructorBean(String value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n\n        public String value() {\n            return value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EnhancedJavaAccessContextFactory extends ContextFactory {\n        @Override\n        protected boolean hasFeature(Context context, int featureIndex) {\n            if (featureIndex == Context.FEATURE_ENHANCED_JAVA_ACCESS) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            return super.hasFeature(context, featureIndex);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
