\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating permission checks**\\n\\nI'm looking at the SecurityManager's checkPermission method and wondering how it handles context. If we're checking for \\\"accessDeclaredMembers,\\\" I think we could inspect the stack and deny access based on the class context. However, using `getClassContext()` could deny too much access, especially concerning ClassCache. It seems we need to limit access based on the target class and consider setting a ThreadLocal boolean to manage initial access checks.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1Odh3z2XLVcwtTfgJfms2SM7|fc_051786af27bb3399016a288ec4b8488194b35455fa0f9b88eb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/user-code-filter.json", "offset": 1, "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 523, "output": 929, "cacheRead": 54784, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56236, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781042857296, "responseId": "resp_051786af27bb3399016a288eaa28f881949724f686db9f4a9d"}}
